The equation \(z^4 + z^2 + 1 = 0\) factors as \((z^2 + z + 1)(z^2 - z + 1) = 0\), so its roots are the primitive 6th roots of unity: \(e^{\pm i\pi/3}\) and \(e^{\pm 2i\pi/3}\).  
These are all 6th roots of unity, and the smallest \(n\) for which they are all \(n\)th roots of unity is \(n = 6\).  

\boxed{6}
